  "prompt": "How do you clear your Hotmail inbox?",
  "response": "To clear your Hotmail (now Outlook.com) inbox, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open Outlook.com and sign in to your account\n\n2. In your inbox, you can:\n- Select multiple emails by clicking the checkbox next to each email\n- Click \"Select all\" at the top of the inbox to choose all emails\n- Click the trash or delete icon to remove selected emails\n\n3. Alternatively, you can:\n- Create folders to organize emails\n- Use the \"Delete\" or \"Archive\" buttons\n- Empty your trash/deleted items folder\n\n4. For a mass cleanup:\n- Use the search bar to find specific types of emails\n- Sort emails by date or sender\n- Delete emails in bulk\n\n5. To automatically manage emails:\n- Set up rules to automatically delete or move certain emails\n- Use inbox filters to organize incoming messages\n\nRemember to save any important emails before deleting them permanently.",
